%% Diagram: How libuv emulates a completion API on top of readiness epoll
%% Type: sequence
sequenceDiagram
    participant App as User code
    participant EL as Event loop thread
    participant Kern as Linux kernel epoll
    participant Sock as Non-blocking socket fd

    App->>EL: uv_read_start(stream, alloc_cb, read_cb)
    EL->>Kern: epoll_ctl(ADD, fd, EPOLLIN, level-triggered)
    Note over EL,Kern: Registration may be batched via io_uring (always-on as of v1.50.0)
    EL->>Kern: epoll_pwait(timeout = next_due_timer_ms)
    Note over Kern: Event loop thread blocks and CPU is yielded
    Sock-->>Kern: TCP segments arrive, fd readable
    Kern-->>EL: epoll_pwait returns: fd EPOLLIN
    EL->>App: alloc_cb(handle, suggested_size, &buf)
    EL->>Sock: read(fd, buf.base, buf.len) — non-blocking
    Sock-->>EL: bytes (or EAGAIN, or 0 = EOF)
    EL->>App: read_cb(stream, nread, &buf)
    Note over EL,App: User sees a completion-style callback, even though Linux only signalled readiness.
